    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.5212/33.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Referring to previous
                    correspondence in regard to the expulsion from Mexico of the Spanish Minister at
                    Mexico City, I beg to inform you that the Department is in receipt of a telegram
                    from Mr. John R. Silliman, dated at Vera Cruz, March 2, stating that a formal
                    reply to his representations has not yet been received, but that both the
                    Secretary of Gobernacion and the Secretary of Foreign Relations have informed
                    Mr. Silliman personally that the case of the Spanish Minister could not be
                    reconsidered.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
